# Crux Dashboard — app/(app)/

## Routes
- /dashboard           — home, recent sessions, quick start
- /dashboard/new       — new session input + submit
- /dashboard/sessions  — all sessions history
- /dashboard/sessions/[id] — live session viewer
- /dashboard/agents    — agent profile manager
- /dashboard/skills    — skills library
- /dashboard/settings  — account, billing, API keys

## App Layout: app/(app)/layout.tsx
Sidebar (240px) + main content area:

Sidebar sections:
- Top: Crux logo + "Beta" pill
- New Session button (full-width, glow)
- Nav: Dashboard, Sessions, Agents, Skills, Settings
- Bottom: User avatar + name + plan badge + "Upgrade" button

## Dashboard Home /dashboard
- "Good morning, {name}" greeting
- Quick-start input: large textarea + submit
- "Recent Sessions" — last 5 session cards
- "Suggested Goals" — 4 pre-written prompt chips

## New Session /dashboard/new
Large centered textarea (full focus):
placeholder: "Describe what you want to accomplish..."
Below: Model selector (dropdown), estimated cost display
CTA: "Start Session →"
On submit: creates Firestore session doc → redirects to 
/dashboard/sessions/{new_id}

## Live Session Viewer /dashboard/sessions/[id]
This is the most important page — show agents working in real-time.

Layout (3-column on desktop):
LEFT (280px) — Session info panel:
  - Session title (from query)
  - Status badge (Planning/Running/Complete)
  - Token usage progress bar
  - Cost so far
  - Agent list with status dots

CENTER — Live activity stream:
  SSE event feed. Each event type gets a distinct card:
  - `planning` → Shows execution plan as collapsible tree
  - `agent_start` → Agent card appears with name + task
  - `tool_call` → Indented under agent: "🔍 Searching web..."
  - `token` → Streaming text under agent card (typewriter)
  - `agent_done` → Card gets green checkmark + summary
  - `artifact` → Download card: file icon + name + download btn
  - `done` → Full summary card, total cost, total tokens

RIGHT (320px, desktop only) — Output preview:
  Scrollable area showing final answer as it builds up.
  When complete: rendered markdown output.

## Sessions History /dashboard/sessions
Table view:
Columns: Date | Query (truncated) | Agents | Tokens | Cost | Status
Row click → open session viewer
Filter by: Status, Date range, Cost
Search by query text

## Agent Profile Manager /dashboard/agents
Grid of agent profile cards. Each card shows:
- Agent name + model badge
- Description
- Tools list (pill chips)
- Skills assigned
- Edit / Duplicate / Delete actions
- "Create New Agent" card (dashed border)

Edit modal: form for all agent_profiles fields from Firestore schema.

## Skills Library /dashboard/skills
Grid of skill cards. Each shows:
- Skill name + version badge
- Description
- Active/Inactive toggle
- "View SKILL.md" button → opens modal with full content

## Settings /dashboard/settings
Tabs: Profile | Billing | API Keys | Notifications

Profile: Name, email, avatar upload
Billing: Current plan card, usage this month, upgrade button
API Keys: Generate/revoke personal API keys
```

